<topic id="author-docbook5-transformation-scenarios">
  <title>DocBook 5 Transformation Scenarios</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Transformation Scenarios<indexterm>DocBook 5</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>DocBook 5 document type<indexterm>Transformation
          scenarios</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>DocBook 5 transformations</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>Built-in transformation scenarios allow you to transform DocBook 5 documents to a variety of
      outputs, such as WebHelp, PDF, HTML, HTML Chunk, XHTML, XHTML Chunk, and EPUB. <ph
        keyref="product"/> also includes a DocBook 5.1 transformation scenario for <i>Assembly</i>
      documents. All of them are listed in the <uicontrol>DocBook 5</uicontrol> section in the <xref
        href="configure-transformation-dialog.dita#configure-transformation-dialog"
          ><uicontrol>Configure Transformation Scenario(s)</uicontrol> dialog box</xref>.</p>
  </body>
